parameters.description: Log maximum nutrient effect multiplier on COTS larval survival and recruitment (currently inactive - nutrient data not available)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log maximum recruitment multiplier during high nutrient conditions. Represents the fold-increase in larval survival when phytoplankton food is abundant. Literature suggests 5-20x increase in larval survival during nutrient pulses. Default exp(1.609)=5x, range exp(0.693)=2x to exp(2.303)=10x. Currently inactive as nutrient data is not available in the dataset.

parameters.description: Log nutrient level at which recruitment enhancement is half-maximal (currently inactive - nutrient data not available)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log half-saturation constant for nutrient effect on recruitment. This is the nutrient level (in same units as nutrient_dat) where the recruitment boost is halfway between baseline and maximum. Should be estimated from data to match the typical nutrient levels associated with outbreak initiation. Currently inactive as nutrient data is not available.

parameters.description: Log steepness parameter controlling sharpness of nutrient response curve (currently inactive - nutrient data not available)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log Hill coefficient for nutrient response. Controls how sharply recruitment responds to nutrient availability. exp(0)=1 gives hyperbolic (Michaelis-Menten) response, exp(0.693)=2 gives sigmoidal response with sharper threshold, exp(1.609)=5 gives very sharp threshold. Higher values create more switch-like outbreak dynamics. Currently inactive as nutrient data is not available.
